WEBVTT

00:05.797 --> 00:09.676
[light orchestral music]

00:09.759 --> 00:12.679
[bell tolling]

00:12.762 --> 00:19.853
♪ ♪

00:21.604 --> 00:24.733
- [breathing heavily]

00:27.902 --> 00:29.320
[door slams]

00:29.404 --> 00:31.281
Hey, hey.
Uh, I need to see my wife.

00:31.364 --> 00:33.074
I need to know if she's okay.
Please!

00:33.158 --> 00:34.701
Stop!
Please!

00:34.784 --> 00:36.161
[grunts]

00:38.246 --> 00:40.039
[grunts]

00:40.957 --> 00:42.751
[exhales heavily]

00:44.210 --> 00:47.130
[monitor beeping]

00:47.213 --> 00:50.133
[machine clicking]

00:50.216 --> 00:53.136
[dramatic music]

00:53.219 --> 01:00.310
♪ ♪

01:05.732 --> 01:07.942
- Morning, sleepyhead.

01:09.736 --> 01:11.821
- What are you doing awake
so early?

01:11.905 --> 01:14.616
- I have a photo shoot
this morning.

01:14.699 --> 01:16.701
- Hmm.

01:16.785 --> 01:18.828
Course you do.

01:18.912 --> 01:20.580
You're a big star.

01:21.915 --> 01:24.417
Come back to bed.
- No. No time for that.

01:24.501 --> 01:26.377
Got hair and makeup
coming any minute.

01:27.837 --> 01:29.047
- Hmm.

01:31.800 --> 01:33.676
It's amazing,
what you've done, Sand.

01:33.760 --> 01:35.345
- Mm.

01:35.428 --> 01:37.889
Well, Dad takes
all the credit.

01:37.972 --> 01:39.974
- Course he does.

01:40.058 --> 01:42.185
But this is all you,
you know that.

01:43.561 --> 01:44.896
- They'll be here soon.

01:44.979 --> 01:46.856
- You don't need them.
You're already gorgeous.

01:46.940 --> 01:49.067
- Mm.

01:49.150 --> 01:50.610
- [chuckles]

01:55.114 --> 01:57.408
[door bangs open]
- Morning, Sandra!

01:57.492 --> 02:00.203
- There she is.
- You look gorgeous.

02:00.286 --> 02:02.288
- [speaking Spanish]

02:02.372 --> 02:03.748
- Do you know what
you're wearing today, darling?

02:03.832 --> 02:05.333
- No, I don't.
- No?

02:05.416 --> 02:08.002
- What do you think?
- [gasps] I love it.

02:08.086 --> 02:09.963
I love it.
- Ooh.

02:10.046 --> 02:11.798
- Yeah?
- Yeah, these are perfect.

02:11.881 --> 02:13.049
I would say
maybe red lipstick?

02:13.132 --> 02:14.509
What do you think?

02:14.592 --> 02:15.718
- The red lip.
- The red lip, I think, yeah.

02:15.802 --> 02:17.345
No, this is perfect.

02:17.428 --> 02:19.639
Did you see?
You're on the front page again.

02:19.722 --> 02:21.683
- Oh, my God.

02:21.766 --> 02:25.728
- Terrible what happened,
but look at you, darling.

02:25.812 --> 02:27.063
- Right, I'll be off, then.

02:27.146 --> 02:28.731
- All right, bye, Alfie.

02:28.815 --> 02:30.817
I look tired.

02:30.900 --> 02:32.485
- No. [laughs]

02:32.569 --> 02:34.571
[Procol Harum's
"Something Following Me"]

02:34.654 --> 02:37.282
- ♪ I hear a weird noise ♪

02:37.365 --> 02:38.783
♪ ♪

02:38.867 --> 02:40.243
♪ Take a look up and down ♪

02:40.326 --> 02:42.203
- All right, mate.
- All right, Alfie.

02:42.287 --> 02:43.872
- Thank you.

02:43.955 --> 02:45.081
Cheers.

02:45.164 --> 02:47.417
- ♪ Cause of the commotion ♪

02:47.500 --> 02:50.128
♪ Is right there
on the ground ♪

02:50.211 --> 02:52.338
♪ ♪

02:52.422 --> 02:54.674
♪ Imagine my surprise ♪

02:54.757 --> 02:56.467
- Morning.

02:56.551 --> 02:59.470
This looks much better.
- Oh, thank you.

02:59.554 --> 03:01.639
Mr. Pennyworth,
I've had a few calls

03:01.723 --> 03:03.433
from your mother already.

03:03.516 --> 03:05.101
Apparently there's been
some trouble

03:05.184 --> 03:06.477
at the Wayne house.

03:06.561 --> 03:08.563
- What kind of trouble?
- I don't know.

03:08.646 --> 03:10.356
But she said you have
to call her right away.

03:10.440 --> 03:11.774
[knock at door]

03:11.858 --> 03:13.318
Ah, good morning, sir.

03:13.401 --> 03:16.321
- Good morning, I'm looking
for Alfred Pennyworth.

03:16.404 --> 03:17.864
- You found him.

03:18.865 --> 03:20.491
- My name is Patrick Wayne.

03:20.575 --> 03:22.160
I understand you know
my family.

03:22.243 --> 03:23.453
- Yeah, that's right.

03:23.536 --> 03:25.330
What can I do for you,
Mr. Wayne?

03:25.413 --> 03:29.000
- My son tried and failed
to kill his wife.

03:29.083 --> 03:31.419
- What?
He never.

03:31.502 --> 03:34.380
- Hard to believe, I know,
but, sadly, true.

03:34.464 --> 03:37.342
He's been locked up
in the Tower of London.

03:37.425 --> 03:38.885
I need you to break him out.

03:40.678 --> 03:43.640
[adventurous music]

03:43.723 --> 03:50.813
♪ ♪

04:33.147 --> 04:35.191
He was taken
straight to the Tower,

04:35.274 --> 04:37.694
and there's been
no contact since.

04:37.777 --> 04:40.154
- I presume you've tried
the legal route.

04:40.238 --> 04:41.614
- Our lawyers
are getting nowhere.

04:41.698 --> 04:43.116
I need to know
Thomas is safe.

04:43.199 --> 04:44.909
- And Martha?

04:44.993 --> 04:46.327
- She's in surgery.

04:46.411 --> 04:48.538
A tragedy,
but nothing we can do for now.

04:49.455 --> 04:52.166
There'll be a plane waiting
to take Thomas back to Gotham.

04:52.250 --> 04:53.459
He'll ride it out there

04:53.543 --> 04:55.086
until we get
to the bottom of this.

04:55.169 --> 04:57.672
- There's a chance all of this
will get worked out.

04:57.755 --> 04:59.549
The authorities tend
to look favorably

04:59.632 --> 05:01.467
on families like yours.

05:01.551 --> 05:03.803
And I expect there's
mitigating circumstances,

05:03.886 --> 05:04.971
as they say.

05:06.723 --> 05:09.350
I have a sneaking suspicion
he was drugged.

05:09.434 --> 05:10.977
- Why do you say that?

05:11.060 --> 05:13.062
- Wild guess.

05:13.146 --> 05:14.564
Was he?

05:14.647 --> 05:16.315
- Who knows what happened?

05:16.399 --> 05:18.901
I'm not taking the chance
of having my son rot

05:18.985 --> 05:20.486
in an English jail cell.

05:20.570 --> 05:21.779
I need him out tonight.

05:21.863 --> 05:24.574
- Well, I'm sorry.
I can't help you.

05:24.657 --> 05:26.284
- Is the Tower that tough?

05:26.367 --> 05:28.953
- No, getting him out
would be a doddle.

05:29.037 --> 05:30.830
It's what happens after.

05:30.913 --> 05:32.373
I'd be hanging myself,
wouldn't I?

05:32.457 --> 05:35.418
Rozzers chasing me
the rest of my life.

05:35.501 --> 05:36.753
- Name your price.

05:36.836 --> 05:38.755
- Mate, I wouldn't do it
for a million quid.

05:38.838 --> 05:40.006
- Really?

05:40.089 --> 05:41.591
'Cause that's
a reasonable price.

05:41.674 --> 05:44.260
- Get out.
- I'm serious.

05:44.343 --> 05:46.429
- A million pounds sterling?

05:47.889 --> 05:52.685
- I'm an extremely wealthy man,
and I love my son.

05:52.769 --> 05:54.854
That's £10,000.

05:54.937 --> 05:56.898
An advance.

05:56.981 --> 06:00.610
My son seemed to think
that for the right price,

06:00.693 --> 06:03.529
there's nothing you can't do.

06:03.613 --> 06:05.448
Was he wrong?

06:05.531 --> 06:08.618
- [breathes deeply]

06:11.079 --> 06:12.830
I'll look into it.

06:12.914 --> 06:14.415
See if there's a way.

06:14.499 --> 06:17.043
No promises.
- Thank you, Mr. Pennyworth.

06:18.252 --> 06:20.797
You have my family's gratitude.

06:30.723 --> 06:33.559
[dial tone rattling]

06:33.643 --> 06:36.437
- [humming]

06:37.980 --> 06:41.150
[phone ringing]

06:41.234 --> 06:43.361
- Is that Mummy?

06:43.444 --> 06:44.987
- You finish your milk,
there's a good girl.

06:45.071 --> 06:48.157
[ringing continues]

06:51.869 --> 06:53.663
Hello.
- Mum.

06:53.746 --> 06:55.164
It's me.
- [sighs]

06:55.248 --> 06:56.999
- I heard about what happened.
Are you all right?

06:57.083 --> 07:00.419
- Oh, Alfie,
it was awful.

07:00.503 --> 07:01.671
He nearly killed her.

07:01.754 --> 07:05.466
- Are you okay?
- Yeah, I'm fine.

07:05.550 --> 07:07.760
I've got Samantha
here with me.

07:07.844 --> 07:09.929
Poor Martha's in hospital.

07:10.012 --> 07:12.682
It's touch and go,
they say.

07:12.765 --> 07:14.517
He was not right, Alfie.

07:14.600 --> 07:17.145
Something happened to him,
like he was possessed.

07:17.228 --> 07:18.354
I had to bash him
over the head

07:18.437 --> 07:19.772
to make him stop.

07:19.856 --> 07:21.524
- Well, you done him a favor.
And Martha.

07:21.607 --> 07:23.192
- Well, I forgot
me head scarf.

07:23.276 --> 07:24.861
I had to go back for it.

07:24.944 --> 07:27.029
I dread to think what would
have happened if I--well...

07:27.113 --> 07:29.031
- What was he like
before you left?

07:29.115 --> 07:32.535
- Fine,
nothing out of the ordinary.

07:32.618 --> 07:34.495
He was just making dinner,
God love him.

07:34.579 --> 07:37.748
- No idea what set him off?
- No.

07:37.832 --> 07:39.167
But he was not himself.

07:41.878 --> 07:43.963
- Hmm.
- I suppose I shouldn't ask

07:44.046 --> 07:45.339
where you were last night.

07:45.423 --> 07:47.592
- Not now, Mum.

07:47.675 --> 07:49.302
What do you know
about his dad?

07:49.385 --> 07:50.678
- Not much.

07:50.761 --> 07:52.096
Bit uppity.

07:52.180 --> 07:53.389
He's got a younger girlfriend.

07:53.472 --> 07:54.682
She's a right madam.

07:54.765 --> 07:56.309
Asked me to dry clean
her delicates,

07:56.392 --> 07:58.603
can you believe it?
- Listen.

07:58.686 --> 07:59.854
The CIA are involved in this,

07:59.937 --> 08:01.314
and I'm not sure
what they want,

08:01.397 --> 08:03.232
but you need to keep
an eye out.

08:03.316 --> 08:05.067
You still got
that Beretta?

08:05.151 --> 08:07.778
- Well, I don't like it,
but yes, I do.

08:07.862 --> 08:11.073
- Good.
Don't take any chances.

08:11.157 --> 08:12.909
You call the office
if there's any trouble.

08:12.992 --> 08:15.620
- All right, love.
You take good care.

08:15.703 --> 08:17.079
- I'll be around later.

08:19.624 --> 08:21.626
- [sighs]

08:26.839 --> 08:30.968
- Did I hear the Tower...
of London?

08:31.052 --> 08:32.553
- Piece of cake.

08:32.637 --> 08:34.263
The Tower's hardly even
a real prison.

08:34.347 --> 08:37.391
More for show.
- Yeah.

08:37.475 --> 08:41.437
So imagine the embarrassment
to the Crown if you do this

08:41.520 --> 08:43.773
and the inevitable
repercussions.

08:43.856 --> 08:45.358
- Tempest in a teapot.

08:45.441 --> 08:46.984
I'm talking about
a million quid here.

08:47.068 --> 08:49.195
- But do you trust him?
- No, of course not.

08:49.278 --> 08:51.447
But we don't need to trust him
to take his money.

08:51.530 --> 08:52.949
And there's several more
of them

08:53.032 --> 08:54.617
once Thomas is safely
on a plane.

08:54.700 --> 08:57.703
- Still...
the Tower of London.

08:57.787 --> 08:59.163
- Stop saying that.

08:59.247 --> 09:00.414
We have made it, Chadley.

09:00.498 --> 09:01.832
We've finally made it.

09:01.916 --> 09:03.334
The world's our oyster.

09:03.417 --> 09:05.795
Now, I'm gonna go see Aziz
and see if I can't

09:05.878 --> 09:06.879
make this easy.

09:06.963 --> 09:08.506
And where the fuck's
Daveboy?

09:10.007 --> 09:12.927
- [breathing deeply]

09:13.010 --> 09:15.930
[peaceful music]

09:16.013 --> 09:22.395
♪ ♪

09:22.478 --> 09:24.480
[sly music]

09:24.563 --> 09:27.525
[floorboards creaking]

09:27.608 --> 09:34.699
♪ ♪

09:44.917 --> 09:46.877
Oh, fuck.

09:52.425 --> 09:55.469
- Stealing away
before I'm awake?

09:55.553 --> 09:56.679
Terrible.

09:56.762 --> 09:58.306
- I'm just trying
to get out of your hair.

09:59.765 --> 10:02.476
- That was a wild night.

10:04.478 --> 10:06.105
- Aye, it was that.

10:06.188 --> 10:08.024
- Is there somewhere
you'd rather be?

10:08.107 --> 10:10.234
- No, just--
just work, you know?

10:10.318 --> 10:11.902
- I thought you said
you were in the army.

10:11.986 --> 10:14.697
- I was.
Private sector now.

10:14.780 --> 10:16.532
- Oh.

10:16.615 --> 10:19.910
I rather liked the idea
of you in uniform.

10:19.994 --> 10:22.830
So what do you do, then?

10:22.913 --> 10:24.749
- Pennyworth Security.

10:24.832 --> 10:27.585
Missing persons,
bodyguarding.

10:27.668 --> 10:30.046
The government throws us
a few jobs.

10:30.129 --> 10:31.714
- Do you ever meet
any P-dubs?

10:31.797 --> 10:33.007
- [chuckling] Aye.

10:33.090 --> 10:34.175
Too many of the bastards.

10:34.258 --> 10:36.344
- Have you met
Captain Blighty?

10:36.427 --> 10:38.179
- Aye.
Aye, you could say that.

10:38.262 --> 10:40.348
- Oh, he sort of scares me.

10:40.431 --> 10:42.016
- Mm, good reason.

10:42.099 --> 10:44.894
He was a mad bastard
before the enhancements.

10:45.895 --> 10:48.606
- There's a party tonight
at the gallery I work at.

10:48.689 --> 10:50.066
Do you want to come?

10:50.149 --> 10:51.984
I'd love you to meet
my friends.

10:52.068 --> 10:53.903
- A gallery?

10:53.986 --> 10:55.446
- Yes, well,
it's an intimate gathering

10:55.529 --> 10:57.615
before the art show
this weekend.

10:57.698 --> 10:59.450
It'll be amazing.

10:59.533 --> 11:02.119
It's a multimedia critique
of the normative.

11:02.203 --> 11:04.830
It's an exploration
in expanding

11:04.914 --> 11:07.249
the bounds
of the British psyche.

11:09.418 --> 11:11.337
- Get tae fuck.
[chuckles]

11:16.258 --> 11:18.094
Well, of course I'll--
I'll come if--

11:18.177 --> 11:21.305
if you want me to,
obviously.

11:21.389 --> 11:22.932
Always been interested
in the British psyche.

11:23.015 --> 11:24.600
- [giggles]
Wonderful.

11:24.683 --> 11:26.894
It's Green Street,
next to the cobbler's.

11:26.977 --> 11:28.813
Starts at 9:00.
- Right.

11:32.316 --> 11:34.652
I can't wait.

11:34.735 --> 11:37.488
I'll see you there.
- Mm, can't wait.

11:48.541 --> 11:50.918
- Turned out really well.

11:51.001 --> 11:52.628
- Can I?

11:54.004 --> 11:55.339
- Go on, then.

11:56.549 --> 11:57.967
[doorbell rings]

12:00.553 --> 12:03.597
Now, you stay right just there.
Okay, love?

12:04.723 --> 12:07.643
[clock ticking]

12:07.726 --> 12:10.104
[tense music]

12:10.187 --> 12:11.397
- [humming]

12:11.480 --> 12:13.232
- [sighs]

12:13.315 --> 12:14.817
[gun cocking]

12:14.900 --> 12:19.155
♪ ♪

12:19.238 --> 12:20.739
Oh, bloody hell.

12:25.369 --> 12:27.663
- Good morning.
- Who are you?

12:27.746 --> 12:29.457
- I'm Roger.

12:29.540 --> 12:30.958
Roger Hammond?

12:31.041 --> 12:32.543
- What do you want?
I'm not buying anything.

12:32.626 --> 12:35.713
- No.
No, I'm here for you.

12:37.756 --> 12:39.216
Divorcé?

12:39.300 --> 12:41.010
I enjoy bird-watching?

12:41.093 --> 12:42.470
I have a Yorkshire terrier?

12:43.262 --> 12:46.056
From the Lonely Hearts.
- Oh, yeah.

12:46.140 --> 12:48.434
I remember now.
- Yeah.

12:49.602 --> 12:50.686
- Just a minute.

12:52.229 --> 12:54.398
[exhales heavily]

12:54.482 --> 12:55.649
Right.

13:02.698 --> 13:04.074
I'm sorry, Roger,

13:04.158 --> 13:07.077
but I'm not doing
that sort of thing anymore.

13:07.161 --> 13:08.120
Full of perverts,

13:08.204 --> 13:10.039
in my limited experience.

13:10.122 --> 13:11.874
- Oh.

13:11.957 --> 13:13.959
Right.
That's disappointing.

13:14.043 --> 13:15.377
I've come from Plumstead.

13:15.461 --> 13:16.879
- Oh, that is a long way.

13:16.962 --> 13:18.380
- Two buses.

13:18.464 --> 13:20.716
- I meant to cancel, but...

13:20.799 --> 13:22.885
I've had me hands full
over here.

13:22.968 --> 13:24.678
I don't--
- Hello.

13:24.762 --> 13:26.889
- Oh, hello.

13:26.972 --> 13:28.432
Sorry for disturbing
your mum here.

13:28.516 --> 13:30.142
- Mum?
[laughs]

13:30.226 --> 13:31.435
Get away.

13:31.519 --> 13:32.686
I'm her nanny.

13:35.648 --> 13:37.441
Well, you're welcome to come in

13:37.525 --> 13:39.443
and have a cup of tea, Roger,

13:39.527 --> 13:42.404
use the facilities before you
make your way back home.

13:42.488 --> 13:43.906
- I wouldn't want to impose.

13:43.989 --> 13:45.658
- No.
Come in, come in.

13:50.329 --> 13:51.580
Oh, thank you.

13:51.664 --> 13:53.916
- Yeah.
- Please.

13:56.043 --> 13:58.420
Can you find a vase?
Well done, darling.

13:58.504 --> 14:01.423
[tense music]

14:01.507 --> 14:04.134
♪ ♪

14:04.218 --> 14:07.346
[indistinct chatter]

14:09.181 --> 14:10.391
- [exhales heavily]

14:11.392 --> 14:13.519
Alfred, good morning.

14:13.602 --> 14:14.937
- Busy round here today.

14:15.020 --> 14:17.356
- Yes, I'm afraid everyone's
rather distracted

14:17.439 --> 14:19.108
with the Commonwealth Summit.

14:19.191 --> 14:21.068
Preparing to welcome
the great independent nations

14:21.151 --> 14:22.528
of the British Empire.

14:22.611 --> 14:24.655
- Sounds like they want
a bit more independence.

14:24.738 --> 14:26.657
- Can't say I blame them.

14:26.740 --> 14:27.741
What can I do for you?

14:27.825 --> 14:29.743
- Any update on Mrs. Wayne?

14:29.827 --> 14:32.288
- She's in surgery.
No news as of yet.

14:34.373 --> 14:37.376
- You know, I bumped into her
the day before yesterday.

14:37.459 --> 14:38.961
- Is that so?

14:39.044 --> 14:41.630
- At the Inner Peace Ashram.

14:41.714 --> 14:43.507
Martha seemed to think
that the CIA

14:43.591 --> 14:46.010
were testing
a new drug there.

14:46.093 --> 14:48.220
This drug was given
to Jessica Thistle,

14:48.304 --> 14:50.014
and she murdered her parents.

14:50.097 --> 14:53.267
Stands to reason the same thing
happened to Thomas.

14:55.102 --> 14:57.104
- Martha tried
to contact me yesterday.

14:57.187 --> 14:59.690
- Any chance of talking to him?

14:59.773 --> 15:01.483
- Why? What's your
particular interest?

15:01.567 --> 15:03.819
- Well,
just a concerned citizen.

15:03.902 --> 15:06.989
- Hmm!
How very noble of you.

15:07.072 --> 15:09.158
But pointless, I'm afraid.

15:09.241 --> 15:11.410
He claims he has
no memory of the incident.

15:11.493 --> 15:13.245
- He's telling the truth.

15:13.329 --> 15:14.788
You know he's innocent.

15:14.872 --> 15:17.750
- Well, strictly speaking,
he's as guilty as sin.

15:17.833 --> 15:20.044
Besides, the CIA evidently
wanted Thomas in jail,

15:20.127 --> 15:21.503
so that's where he's staying
for now.

15:21.587 --> 15:23.088
- They also wanted
Martha dead.

15:23.172 --> 15:25.090
- Indeed, so she knows
something important.

15:25.174 --> 15:26.675
I'd like to find out
what that is

15:26.759 --> 15:27.843
before further provoking
the Americans

15:27.926 --> 15:29.219
ahead of a global summit.

15:29.303 --> 15:31.347
- Well, yeah, but--
- Stay out of this.

15:32.348 --> 15:34.558
Now is not the time
for you to be meddling

15:34.642 --> 15:36.935
with international relations,
is that clear?

15:39.938 --> 15:41.857
- Say no more.
- Good.

15:43.567 --> 15:46.695
Thomas may not have
done this deliberately,

15:46.779 --> 15:48.364
but he did do it.

15:49.406 --> 15:51.742
The Tower
is the safest place for him,

15:51.825 --> 15:54.078
for his sake and ours.

15:54.161 --> 15:56.455
- Mm.
[line rings]

15:56.538 --> 15:58.207
- Good morning,
Whitehall switchboard.

15:58.290 --> 15:59.667
How may I connect you?

15:59.750 --> 16:02.711
- Yes, I'm trying to reach
Mrs. Martha Wayne.

16:02.795 --> 16:04.046
But I-I keep being--

16:04.129 --> 16:07.216
- Mrs. Wayne is not
available, sir.

16:07.299 --> 16:08.717
Sorry, goodbye.
- Well--

16:08.801 --> 16:10.552
[line clicks, dial tone hums]

16:10.636 --> 16:12.137
[groans]

16:18.227 --> 16:21.313
[phone ringing]

16:23.482 --> 16:26.193
[mysterious music]

16:26.276 --> 16:33.367
♪ ♪

16:43.752 --> 16:45.546
Hello.

16:45.629 --> 16:47.005
- Hello, Dr. Glubb.

16:47.089 --> 16:48.590
How nice to speak
to you at last.

16:48.674 --> 16:50.050
- Who is this?

16:50.134 --> 16:53.679
- I am the answer
to all your prayers.

16:53.762 --> 16:55.597
- How did you find me?

16:55.681 --> 16:57.099
- Just be glad I did.

16:57.182 --> 16:59.435
Shall we meet
to discuss business?

16:59.518 --> 17:02.146
- Who are you?
- Does it matter?

17:02.229 --> 17:05.315
I'm not the CIA, if that's
what you're worried about.

17:05.399 --> 17:06.775
How much longer
do you think

17:06.859 --> 17:08.610
you'll be able
to hide from them?

17:08.694 --> 17:13.031
They are so vicious
and clever.

17:13.115 --> 17:15.242
- Where shall we meet?

17:15.325 --> 17:16.535
- Cheers.

17:16.618 --> 17:18.829
Well, fuck me.

17:20.956 --> 17:22.833
I do not believe that.

17:22.916 --> 17:25.461
Thank God for Mrs. P, yeah?
- Indeed.

17:29.214 --> 17:30.340
- Mmm.

17:30.424 --> 17:32.593
- You're in last night's
clothes again.

17:32.676 --> 17:34.219
You know,
I've said this before,

17:34.303 --> 17:38.098
we should all present
good business decorum.

17:38.182 --> 17:40.642
- Hmm.
Oh.

17:40.726 --> 17:42.936
I went home with a bird
from the funeral last night.

17:43.020 --> 17:45.230
Hmm?
A real smasher.

17:45.314 --> 17:46.648
Posh as fuck.

17:46.732 --> 17:49.735
Proper nice.
- Goodness.

17:49.818 --> 17:52.696
Well, congratulations.

17:52.780 --> 17:54.823
- Nah, I don't know.

17:54.907 --> 17:56.909
There's got to be
a catch somewhere.

17:56.992 --> 17:58.243
She's invited me
to something

17:58.327 --> 18:00.829
at a fucking art gallery,
for fuck's sake,

18:00.913 --> 18:02.164
to meet her fancy friends.

18:02.247 --> 18:04.208
- Why would she want that?
- Exactly.

18:04.291 --> 18:05.667
Why?

18:05.751 --> 18:07.753
- I cannot fathom.

18:07.836 --> 18:09.254
But in future,

18:09.338 --> 18:12.508
please keep some spare clothes
in the office.

18:12.591 --> 18:14.051
Mr. Pennyworth.

18:16.011 --> 18:18.889
- Morning.
- Morning. No luck with Aziz.

18:18.972 --> 18:20.724
He wants to keep
Thomas Wayne locked up.

18:20.808 --> 18:22.601
- Well, that makes sense
after Jessica Thistle.

18:22.684 --> 18:24.561
- Mm.
- We don't know for sure yet

18:24.645 --> 18:25.771
that they're connected.

18:25.854 --> 18:27.439
- Fuck off.

18:27.523 --> 18:28.982
Of course we do.

18:29.066 --> 18:32.820
Thomas Wayne hasn't the balls
to stab his wife.

18:32.903 --> 18:34.863
It was yon CIA.

18:34.947 --> 18:38.033
- Why is the CIA
setting up Thomas Wayne?

18:38.116 --> 18:40.619
- Thomas was the weapon,
not the target.

18:40.702 --> 18:42.287
Martha knew something,

18:42.371 --> 18:43.872
something more than we do,

18:43.956 --> 18:46.166
else we'd be on the wrong end
of the kitchen knife.

18:46.250 --> 18:49.086
So we're still going in.
Tonight.

18:50.170 --> 18:52.214
- [sighs]

18:52.297 --> 18:53.799
- Where?

18:53.882 --> 18:55.300
- The Tower.

18:55.384 --> 18:57.177
We're getting him out.

18:57.261 --> 18:59.137
- Are you fucking joking?

18:59.221 --> 19:01.014
This is not our fight.

19:01.098 --> 19:03.517
Huh, the CIA? The Tower?
Nah.

19:03.600 --> 19:06.603
No, that's deep, dark water
you're wading into.

19:06.687 --> 19:09.273
- His dad's paying us
a million quid.

19:13.151 --> 19:14.486
- A million?

19:14.570 --> 19:16.154
What, a million pounds?

19:16.238 --> 19:18.991
- Sweet, eh?
- I don't know.

19:19.074 --> 19:21.285
That seems too good
to be true, doesn't it?

19:21.368 --> 19:24.163
No one gets a million pounds.
There's got to be a catch.

19:24.246 --> 19:25.747
- Daveboy, do I really
have to say it?

19:25.831 --> 19:29.042
- No, I know, I know.
Who dares fucking wins.

19:29.126 --> 19:32.713
But, Alfie,
a million quid?

19:32.796 --> 19:34.715
- Call Lucius, we're gonna
need him for this one.

19:34.798 --> 19:36.091
- Right away.

19:36.174 --> 19:37.593
- Hey, hold on a wee minute.

19:37.676 --> 19:39.177
We've been sitting here
for ten fucking minutes

19:39.261 --> 19:41.430
eating pink wafers,
and you never thought

19:41.513 --> 19:42.764
to tell me
that we were breaking

19:42.848 --> 19:44.641
into the Tower
of fucking London?

19:46.602 --> 19:47.936
Fuck.

19:49.563 --> 19:50.814
- Can you believe it?

19:50.898 --> 19:52.774
He actually asked me--

19:52.858 --> 19:55.485
- [humming]

19:55.569 --> 19:58.488
- Do you know, I can't tell you
what he asked me.

19:58.572 --> 20:00.073
But they weren't the words
of a gentleman,

20:00.157 --> 20:01.450
I can promise you that.

20:01.533 --> 20:03.952
So I decided I'm not
doing that anymore.

20:04.036 --> 20:06.955
You never know who's on there
or where they've been.

20:07.039 --> 20:09.207
- Goodness.

20:09.291 --> 20:12.377
I'm sorry you had
such an awful experience.

20:12.461 --> 20:14.046
- I just wanted to meet
a nice man

20:14.129 --> 20:15.797
and spend time with him.

20:15.881 --> 20:19.801
Maybe do a bit of dancing.
I used to love dancing.

20:19.885 --> 20:21.303
Do you dance?

20:21.386 --> 20:22.763
- Uh, no.

20:24.389 --> 20:26.058
Two left feet,
I'm afraid.

20:29.061 --> 20:31.396
- Well, you seem
like a nice normal fella.

20:31.480 --> 20:34.566
What are you doing
on Lonely Hearts?

20:34.650 --> 20:35.901
- Well...

20:38.111 --> 20:40.864
My wife left me.

20:40.948 --> 20:42.699
- Terrible business, terrible.

20:42.783 --> 20:46.578
- She ran off
with Clive Vickery, actually.

20:46.662 --> 20:49.539
- Clive Vickery
of "Good Day Britain"?

20:49.623 --> 20:52.167
[gasps]
Oh.

20:52.250 --> 20:56.463
I do actually remember
hearing about that.

20:56.546 --> 20:58.090
- Yes.

20:58.173 --> 20:59.758
Most people did.

21:01.426 --> 21:04.221
Whole thing was...

21:04.304 --> 21:05.681
very embarrassing.

21:10.435 --> 21:12.229
- That's my husband.

21:12.312 --> 21:14.523
God rest his soul.

21:14.606 --> 21:16.191
Arthur.

21:17.651 --> 21:19.945
- Is--but he--

21:21.363 --> 21:23.031
The prime minister.

21:23.115 --> 21:24.449
And almost the queen.

21:24.533 --> 21:27.577
- He got mixed up
in a lot of nonsense.

21:27.661 --> 21:30.205
But he wasn't all bad.
You should know that.

21:31.999 --> 21:34.209
Died twice, you know.

21:34.292 --> 21:35.293
- I'm sorry?

21:35.377 --> 21:37.754
- So what I'm saying is,

21:37.838 --> 21:40.090
you've no need
to be embarrassed.

21:40.173 --> 21:41.967
Not in front of me, anyway.

21:42.050 --> 21:43.343
- Well, no.

21:45.262 --> 21:46.555
Indeed.

21:46.638 --> 21:49.683
- You know, I never trusted
Clive Vickery.

21:49.766 --> 21:52.602
His eyes
are too close together.

21:52.686 --> 21:55.564
[laughter]

21:57.816 --> 21:59.484
[metallic clanging]

21:59.568 --> 22:01.069
- [sighs]

22:01.153 --> 22:03.822
[dramatic music]

22:03.905 --> 22:08.660
♪ ♪

22:08.744 --> 22:12.164
[grunting]

22:13.123 --> 22:14.875
[keys jangling, lock clicks]

22:14.958 --> 22:17.919
[footsteps tapping]

22:19.546 --> 22:20.881
Please, I'm begging you.

22:20.964 --> 22:22.007
I need to know
if my wife's alive.

22:22.090 --> 22:24.092
I need to know if she--

22:24.176 --> 22:25.927
I need to know
if she's okay.

22:28.305 --> 22:29.848
[door slams]

22:29.931 --> 22:37.022
♪ ♪

22:45.405 --> 22:47.616
[boat horn blares]

22:49.326 --> 22:50.452
- Yes, uh-huh.

22:50.535 --> 22:52.287
- Okay, now,
I need all of this back,

22:52.370 --> 22:54.039
so don't leave anything behind.

22:54.122 --> 22:55.373
- What the fuck is that?

22:55.457 --> 22:58.126
- This here
is a lock-picking device.

22:58.210 --> 22:59.419
- Hmm.

22:59.503 --> 23:01.213
- Once securely fastened
to the keyhole...

23:03.548 --> 23:04.925
Press this lever,

23:05.008 --> 23:06.968
and the door should unlock
within ten seconds.

23:07.052 --> 23:08.970
- Yes, miss, I'll hold.

23:09.054 --> 23:10.347
- Should?

23:10.430 --> 23:12.140
For fuck's sake.

23:12.224 --> 23:13.725
Does it work, or does it not?

23:13.809 --> 23:15.477
- I don't need to be here.

23:15.560 --> 23:17.646
You know?

23:17.729 --> 23:20.774
In fact, I shouldn't be here.

23:20.857 --> 23:22.651
- No, we're very grateful
that you are here.

23:22.734 --> 23:24.986
Shut up, Daveboy.

23:25.070 --> 23:26.530
- Now, you may not know this,

23:26.613 --> 23:29.157
but I'm quite
an avid mountaineer.

23:29.241 --> 23:31.952
And I've been toying
with several ideas

23:32.035 --> 23:33.912
in that regard.

23:33.995 --> 23:36.248
Now, I'll explain--
- Grappling hook gun, is it?

23:36.331 --> 23:38.166
Give her here.

23:38.250 --> 23:39.417
- Uh, yes,

23:39.501 --> 23:42.712
that's--that's exactly
what that is.

23:42.796 --> 23:44.756
How it works--
- You shoot it at your target,

23:44.840 --> 23:47.008
flick the switch on the side,
and away you go.

23:48.969 --> 23:51.138
- Yes.
- Think I got it.

23:53.431 --> 23:55.392
- Well, you've got
a second one of them somewhere?

23:56.935 --> 23:58.436
Well, how do I get up
the bleeding wall?

23:58.520 --> 24:01.690
- When Alfie gets there,

24:01.773 --> 24:03.108
he'll throw down a rope.

24:04.776 --> 24:05.735
You climb up.

24:05.819 --> 24:08.363
- Oh, that's fucking perfect.

24:08.446 --> 24:09.906
- Fantastic.
- [laughs]

24:09.990 --> 24:12.909
- Now, I must emphasize
these are prototypes.

24:12.993 --> 24:15.120
I've only conducted
limited testing,

24:15.203 --> 24:17.080
some more successful
than others.

24:17.164 --> 24:18.498
- Are you fucking hearing this?

24:18.582 --> 24:20.250
- It'll be fine.
- Mm-hmm.

24:20.333 --> 24:21.751
Thank you, madam.

24:23.295 --> 24:25.380
Thankfully Mrs. Wayne is safe.

24:25.463 --> 24:27.048
Out of surgery and doing well.

24:27.132 --> 24:28.717
- How's that for a sign?

24:28.800 --> 24:30.552
Boots on, Daveboy.

24:30.635 --> 24:31.469
- Aye.

24:31.553 --> 24:34.514
[suspenseful music]

24:34.598 --> 24:41.688
♪ ♪

24:52.490 --> 24:53.992
- [groans]

24:54.075 --> 24:55.785
- [panting]

24:55.869 --> 24:57.287
Shit.
[grunts]

25:00.207 --> 25:01.917
Fuck.

25:02.000 --> 25:03.919
Fuck!

25:04.002 --> 25:06.630
[panting]

25:10.175 --> 25:13.303
So, eh, this Sally girl.

25:13.386 --> 25:15.055
- Yeah.

25:15.138 --> 25:17.390
- She--

25:17.474 --> 25:19.517
she asked me
to call her names.

25:19.601 --> 25:22.812
You know, in bed.
Dirty names.

25:22.896 --> 25:24.189
- Did she?

25:24.272 --> 25:26.483
- Do you think that's normal?

25:26.566 --> 25:28.360
- Happens.

25:28.443 --> 25:31.571
- So I called her
a bastard wee hun.

25:31.655 --> 25:32.989
Seemed to do the trick.

25:33.073 --> 25:34.282
- [grunts]

25:34.366 --> 25:36.076
[hook clatters]

25:36.159 --> 25:37.827
Bloody hell, it worked.

25:43.500 --> 25:45.710
- So do you think
that's all right?

25:45.794 --> 25:47.295
- I'd love to stay and chat
about your love life,

25:47.379 --> 25:49.005
but we should crack on, eh?

25:50.840 --> 25:53.301
Now, if I just flip this--

25:53.385 --> 25:54.594
Whoa!

25:57.222 --> 25:59.599
[breathing heavily]

26:04.980 --> 26:07.899
[sly music]

26:07.983 --> 26:12.153
♪ ♪

26:12.237 --> 26:13.697
- Of course.

26:13.780 --> 26:16.783
I'm the one that's
got to climb the bastard.

26:16.866 --> 26:17.784
[grunts]

26:17.867 --> 26:19.744
- [whistling]

26:19.828 --> 26:22.956
- ♪ Tell her how I feel and
maybe get a second glance ♪

26:23.039 --> 26:24.749
♪ Now I got to get used ♪

26:24.833 --> 26:26.293
- Can we turn this off, please?

26:26.376 --> 26:28.003
- ♪ Living next door
to Alice ♪

26:28.086 --> 26:30.672
- It's best to try and relax
on these kind of jobs.

26:30.755 --> 26:32.299
Makes them go faster.

26:32.382 --> 26:35.593
- I can see no reason at all
for relaxation.

26:35.677 --> 26:40.015
- ♪ Carved our initials
in the bark ♪

26:40.098 --> 26:41.266
[radio clicks,
music stops]

26:41.349 --> 26:44.311
- [breathes deeply]

26:44.394 --> 26:47.355
- [grunting]

26:47.439 --> 26:49.607
Fuck's sake.

26:50.984 --> 26:54.070
Not a fucking word.

26:54.154 --> 26:55.363
- [snorts]

26:55.447 --> 26:57.282
- Ugh.

26:59.951 --> 27:03.621
[keys jangling, lock clicks]

27:03.705 --> 27:05.790
[footsteps tapping]
- Watch it, mate.

27:05.874 --> 27:08.626
Now, this is a pickle.
- Alfie.

27:08.710 --> 27:10.211
- All right, let's not
alert the whole Tower.

27:10.295 --> 27:11.963
- How's Martha?
Is she okay? Do you know?

27:12.047 --> 27:13.882
- She's alive.
She's gonna be all right.

27:13.965 --> 27:16.509
- [exhales heavily]
Thank God.

27:17.969 --> 27:19.512
And Samantha?
- She's fine.

27:19.596 --> 27:20.972
She's with Mum.
Now, stand back.

27:21.056 --> 27:22.766
We'll have you out of here
in a jiffy.

27:22.849 --> 27:24.184
- Uh, okay.

27:24.267 --> 27:26.519
- All ready?
Here goes nothing.

27:26.603 --> 27:27.562
[device clicks]

27:27.645 --> 27:34.736
♪ ♪

27:41.451 --> 27:43.912
I fucking knew it.

27:43.995 --> 27:46.247
We should have brought
a bloody blowtorch.

27:46.331 --> 27:48.041
Fuck.

27:48.124 --> 27:52.587
[device buzzes and whirs]

27:52.670 --> 27:59.761
♪ ♪

28:06.726 --> 28:07.852
[cell door creaks]

28:07.936 --> 28:10.772
[chuckles]
Fuck me.

28:11.731 --> 28:13.441
- I didn't do
what they're saying I did.

28:13.525 --> 28:15.777
I was drugged.
I would never hurt her.

28:15.860 --> 28:17.153
- I know that.

28:17.237 --> 28:18.571
Now, if you don't mind,
your dad's paid us

28:18.655 --> 28:20.323
good money
to get you out of here.

28:20.407 --> 28:22.117
- My father came to you?
- Yeah.

28:22.200 --> 28:23.827
Now, give us your hands.

28:23.910 --> 28:25.120
- What's happening?

28:25.203 --> 28:26.454
- We're prisoners,

28:26.538 --> 28:29.082
and Daveboy's escorting us
out of here.

28:29.165 --> 28:30.375
[handcuffs click]

28:33.795 --> 28:35.797
- You hang in there, mate.

28:35.880 --> 28:37.841
- Every bleedin' night--

28:38.967 --> 28:40.343
Hold on.

28:44.514 --> 28:45.932
[cell door bangs]

28:47.517 --> 28:50.395
[alarm blaring]

28:54.941 --> 28:56.818
- Oh, dear.

28:56.901 --> 28:59.988
- It's okay.
What's plan B?

29:00.071 --> 29:01.948
- Plan B, sir?
- Plan B,

29:02.031 --> 29:04.826
for when plan A goes
completely fucking haywire!

29:04.909 --> 29:06.161
There's always a plan B.

29:06.244 --> 29:07.829
- Mr. Pennyworth
was very confident

29:07.912 --> 29:09.581
in his plan, sir.

29:10.290 --> 29:12.667
[machine guns firing]

29:12.750 --> 29:13.793
- Those were machine guns.

29:13.877 --> 29:15.587
- I do see your point, however.

29:15.670 --> 29:18.506
Having a plan B
or, if I may call it,

29:18.590 --> 29:20.717
a backup plan
might have been helpful

29:20.800 --> 29:23.511
at this juncture.
- [gasps]

29:23.595 --> 29:24.846
We're all going to jail.

29:24.929 --> 29:26.055
- But I still think
it's too early

29:26.139 --> 29:27.599
to give up on plan A.

29:27.682 --> 29:29.392
[gunfire]

29:29.476 --> 29:31.352
- This van isn't bulletproofed.

29:31.436 --> 29:33.188
I should have
bulletproofed the van.

29:33.271 --> 29:35.231
That lightweight alloy
I've been developing.

29:35.315 --> 29:39.152
4-, no, 5-millimeter sheeting
all around.

29:39.235 --> 29:40.695
- That's it, sir.
You think about that.

29:40.778 --> 29:42.322
I'll start the engine.
[engine turning over]

29:42.405 --> 29:43.531
- Where are we going?

29:43.615 --> 29:46.868
[gunfire]
[alarm blaring]

29:46.951 --> 29:54.042
♪ ♪

29:57.795 --> 29:59.047
- All right, sir?

29:59.130 --> 30:00.632
- All right, Chadley,
we can go now.

30:01.466 --> 30:02.383
- Jolly good.

30:02.467 --> 30:04.427
[all grunt]

30:04.511 --> 30:05.803
- Jesus.

30:08.306 --> 30:11.434
- Your plan worked.
- Course it worked.

30:11.518 --> 30:12.977
It was a lovely plan.

30:13.061 --> 30:14.854
Have some faith, Mr. Fox.

30:14.938 --> 30:17.899
[gunfire]

30:17.982 --> 30:19.817
- How are you, Thomas?

30:19.901 --> 30:21.819
- Uh, yeah, well,
I've been better, Lucius,

30:21.903 --> 30:23.905
but, um, thanks for this.

30:23.988 --> 30:27.033
- Oh, hey, just high treason.

30:27.116 --> 30:28.368
No big deal.

30:29.494 --> 30:32.121
- Right, if we're done here,

30:32.205 --> 30:34.958
can you drop me off on the way?

30:35.041 --> 30:36.501
I've got a date.

30:40.171 --> 30:41.297
What?

30:41.381 --> 30:42.632
[knock at door]
- Come in.

30:42.715 --> 30:44.259
[door clicks open]

30:44.342 --> 30:47.095
- Sir, Thomas Wayne
has escaped from the Tower.

30:50.932 --> 30:52.767
- [sighs]

30:52.850 --> 30:54.102
Put out an emergency bulletin

30:54.185 --> 30:56.437
for the arrest
of Alfred Pennyworth.

30:56.521 --> 30:58.273
- Yes, sir.

30:58.356 --> 30:59.649
- [sighs]

30:59.732 --> 31:01.401
[phone beeps]
God damn it.

31:01.484 --> 31:04.821
God damn it!
- What's wrong?

31:04.904 --> 31:06.698
Martha is still alive.

31:06.781 --> 31:09.367
And your damn son
just escaped from the Tower.

31:09.450 --> 31:10.952
- Ah.

31:12.078 --> 31:13.496
- Wait a second.

31:15.373 --> 31:16.749
Did you arrange that?

31:18.585 --> 31:20.128
- He's my only son.

31:20.211 --> 31:21.254
I couldn't let him rot in--

31:21.337 --> 31:22.505
[groans]
- Jesus Christ,

31:22.589 --> 31:23.631
I'm surrounded
by fucking idiots.

31:23.715 --> 31:25.383
- But I don't see the harm.

31:25.466 --> 31:27.468
- If the Brits don't have
a culprit to prosecute,

31:27.552 --> 31:28.720
they'll have to dig deeper,

31:28.803 --> 31:30.179
and they'll start
looking at us.

31:30.263 --> 31:31.931
- But the CIA are untouchable,
aren't they?

31:32.015 --> 31:33.975
- I'm not.
They'll throw me to the dogs.

31:34.058 --> 31:35.268
Claim I'm a rogue agent.

31:35.351 --> 31:36.644
- Are you?
- Of course I am.

31:36.728 --> 31:37.812
Wake up, you dumb motherfucker.

31:37.895 --> 31:39.355
This whole operation is rogue.

31:39.439 --> 31:40.898
The System is rogue.

31:40.982 --> 31:43.234
You're the only square idiot
in this whole damn deal.

31:43.318 --> 31:44.819
[touch tones beeping,
line rings]

31:44.902 --> 31:46.779
It's me.
- Mrs. Wayne is alive.

31:46.863 --> 31:48.156
- Yes, I know.

31:48.239 --> 31:49.282
- What would you like us
to do?

31:49.365 --> 31:50.491
- Do what you have to do,

31:50.575 --> 31:51.659
and then we're
shutting up shop.

31:51.743 --> 31:52.994
- Okay.
- That's right.

31:53.077 --> 31:54.579
Scorched Earth.

31:54.662 --> 31:56.456
- Yes, ma'am.
[line clicks, dial tone hums]

31:56.539 --> 31:59.208
- Scorched Earth?
What the heck does that mean?

31:59.292 --> 32:01.836
- Where is Thomas now?
- I don't know.

32:01.919 --> 32:03.504
[groaning]

32:03.588 --> 32:04.505
- Where is he?

32:04.589 --> 32:07.550
[dramatic music]

32:07.634 --> 32:13.640
♪ ♪

32:13.723 --> 32:14.891
[guns clicking]

32:14.974 --> 32:22.065
♪ ♪

32:56.015 --> 32:57.517
[glass bottle clatters]

32:57.600 --> 33:00.436
[tense music]

33:00.520 --> 33:03.022
- Uh...
- Shh.

33:03.106 --> 33:04.399
[gun cocking]

33:06.526 --> 33:08.569
[door clicks open]
Oh, God.

33:08.653 --> 33:10.571
[door slams]
- Mum?

33:10.655 --> 33:12.031
- [sighs]

33:12.115 --> 33:14.575
For goodness' sake,
you scared me to death.

33:14.659 --> 33:16.828
- Steady on.
You can put that away.

33:17.870 --> 33:20.081
- Alfie, what have you done?

33:20.164 --> 33:22.917
- Business.
Good business.

33:23.000 --> 33:25.586
- I'm sorry for the trouble,
Mrs. Pennyworth.

33:25.670 --> 33:27.630
Where's Samantha?
- She's fine.

33:27.714 --> 33:29.632
She's asleep upstairs.

33:29.716 --> 33:31.718
- Who's this, then?
- Oh, this is Roger.

33:31.801 --> 33:33.010
Never you mind who this is.

33:33.094 --> 33:34.178
- Uh, maybe I should--

33:34.262 --> 33:35.722
- No, you're staying here.

33:35.805 --> 33:37.640
I'm not having Alfie
spoil our evening

33:37.724 --> 33:38.641
with his shenanigans.

33:38.725 --> 33:40.017
- Daddy!
- Sam!

33:40.101 --> 33:41.519
- Daddy!
- Come here, sweetie.

33:41.602 --> 33:44.480
Oh, it's good to see you.

33:44.564 --> 33:46.816
- Me and Mary made a cake.
- You did?

33:46.899 --> 33:48.943
Oh, delicious.
I'll have to have a slice.

33:49.026 --> 33:50.153
[chuckles]

33:50.236 --> 33:51.487
- So is this
your boyfriend, then?

33:51.571 --> 33:53.948
- Shush, you.
We only met today.

33:54.031 --> 33:55.324
- I see.

33:55.408 --> 33:57.618
- Well, don't be giving me
that face.

33:57.702 --> 33:59.203
I can have a boyfriend
if I like.

33:59.287 --> 34:00.621
- Well...yeah.

34:00.705 --> 34:01.664
- I can dance down the street

34:01.748 --> 34:02.665
naked with him if I like.

34:02.749 --> 34:04.208
- Uh, I assure you, sir,

34:04.292 --> 34:05.752
that's not at all
what I had in mind.

34:05.835 --> 34:07.170
- No, no.

34:07.253 --> 34:08.379
It's Liberty Hall here, mate.

34:08.463 --> 34:09.672
You do as you please.

34:09.756 --> 34:11.841
- I better go.

34:11.924 --> 34:13.050
Goodbye.

34:14.218 --> 34:15.762
Nice meeting you, but, uh--

34:15.845 --> 34:16.971
goodbye!

34:17.054 --> 34:18.473
- Is Mummy all right?
[door slams]

34:18.556 --> 34:20.767
- Thank you, Alfie.
Thank you very much.

34:24.395 --> 34:25.980
- I'll give you ten minutes
with Samantha,

34:26.063 --> 34:28.149
and then we'd better get
to the airport, all right?

34:29.484 --> 34:31.986
- Uh, Mrs. Pennyworth,
would--would you mind--

34:32.069 --> 34:33.321
- Yes, of course I will.

34:33.404 --> 34:34.989
Come on, then, darling.

34:35.072 --> 34:36.532
Let's see what's left to do.

34:36.616 --> 34:38.201
- There is nothing.

34:38.284 --> 34:40.328
- Alfie.

34:40.411 --> 34:41.996
I'm not leaving my family.

34:42.079 --> 34:44.165
- Well, you can't help Martha,
can you?

34:44.248 --> 34:46.125
And Sam's safe here with Mum.

34:46.209 --> 34:47.835
You stay in London,
you'll be back to the Tower--

34:47.919 --> 34:50.463
- I'm not going anywhere.
- It's not up to you.

34:50.546 --> 34:52.173
Your dad's paying us
to get you out of the country,

34:52.256 --> 34:53.257
so that's what we're gonna do.

34:53.341 --> 34:54.300
- Fuck my dad.

34:54.383 --> 34:56.052
- That's my favorite towel.

34:58.012 --> 35:00.890
- I think he is responsible
for all of this.

35:00.973 --> 35:02.642
- Do you have any proof?

35:02.725 --> 35:04.685
- Wayne Enterprises
was developing

35:04.769 --> 35:06.771
a mind-control drug
with the CIA.

35:06.854 --> 35:08.648
Operation Lullaby State.

35:08.731 --> 35:10.191
The doctor running it
has gone rogue,

35:10.274 --> 35:11.317
and now he's trying
to sell the stuff

35:11.400 --> 35:12.527
to the highest bidder.

35:12.610 --> 35:14.195
Martha found out.

35:14.278 --> 35:17.073
- And this Lullaby drug
makes people go nuts?

35:17.156 --> 35:18.533
Could he have given it to you?

35:18.616 --> 35:20.368
- Well, I can't remember
anything that happened

35:20.451 --> 35:21.661
after I got home yesterday,

35:21.744 --> 35:24.372
and now Martha
is in the hospital,

35:24.455 --> 35:26.958
and he's trying
to get me out of the country.

35:27.041 --> 35:28.501
- Not conclusive, really,
is it?

35:28.584 --> 35:29.710
- Of course it is.

35:29.794 --> 35:31.003
He tried to make me kill
my own wife.

35:31.087 --> 35:33.047
- Well, be that as it may,

35:33.130 --> 35:34.715
your dad is paying us
a million pounds

35:34.799 --> 35:36.217
to get you on a plane.

35:36.300 --> 35:37.802
What will you pay to stay?

35:37.885 --> 35:39.345
- I don't have a million pounds
to give you, Alfie.

35:39.428 --> 35:40.888
- There's your answer, then.

35:40.972 --> 35:42.056
- Jesus, really?

35:42.139 --> 35:44.225
- Look, I'm doing you a favor.

35:44.308 --> 35:45.726
What are you gonna do here?

35:45.810 --> 35:47.019
You're a wanted man.

35:47.103 --> 35:49.021
And what you gonna do
with your dad?

35:49.105 --> 35:50.690
Kill him?
Arrest him?

35:50.773 --> 35:52.358
- I-I'll find out the truth.
That's what I'll do.

35:52.441 --> 35:53.526
- Oh, bugger the truth.

35:53.609 --> 35:55.444
Who cares about the truth?

35:55.528 --> 35:56.904
Whereas if you get
on that plane,

35:56.988 --> 35:59.407
I am a millionaire.

35:59.490 --> 36:00.992
- Alfie.

36:01.075 --> 36:03.995
[dire music]

36:04.078 --> 36:07.415
♪ ♪

36:07.498 --> 36:08.499
- [sighs]

36:08.583 --> 36:15.673
♪ ♪

36:17.508 --> 36:18.759
- [laughs]

36:18.843 --> 36:21.971
[indistinct chatter]

36:27.226 --> 36:28.603
- Daveboy?

36:30.396 --> 36:32.231
You came.
- Aye.

36:34.817 --> 36:37.028
- What are you wearing?

36:37.111 --> 36:39.906
- It's a--a long story.

36:39.989 --> 36:43.993
- Well, what do you think?

36:45.119 --> 36:47.413
- Very nice.
- Yes.

36:47.496 --> 36:49.415
It is very special,
isn't it?

36:49.498 --> 36:50.875
- Well, it's better
than those tins of soup,

36:50.958 --> 36:52.293
that's for sure.
- [chuckles]

36:52.376 --> 36:53.794
- Well, I like to think so.

36:55.504 --> 36:59.216
- Sally, what have you
brought us?

36:59.300 --> 37:01.427
- This is Daveboy.

37:01.510 --> 37:04.013
Daveboy, this is
Francis Foulkes.

37:04.096 --> 37:05.973
He's the artist.

37:06.057 --> 37:07.433
- Charmed.

37:07.516 --> 37:08.893
- How you doing there, pal?

37:08.976 --> 37:11.646
It's very, uh, nice art
that you have here.

37:11.729 --> 37:13.606
- Where did you pick him up?

37:13.689 --> 37:15.358
- We met
at the Thistle funeral.

37:15.441 --> 37:16.525
- Ah.

37:16.609 --> 37:17.485
So you witnessed

37:17.568 --> 37:18.819
that inspired performance.

37:18.903 --> 37:20.363
Everyone's
been talking about it.

37:20.446 --> 37:22.657
I'm so sad I missed it.

37:22.740 --> 37:25.117
- That was Daveboy.

37:26.661 --> 37:28.162
- You don't say.

37:29.163 --> 37:31.499
Ingenious!
- Well, I didn't mean to--

37:31.582 --> 37:33.501
- You are fabulous.

37:33.584 --> 37:35.753
Look at this face.
[gasps]

37:35.836 --> 37:38.881
Plebeian angst in the flesh.
[sighs]

37:38.965 --> 37:41.968
It's a pleasure to meet you,
Dave...boy.

37:42.051 --> 37:44.345
- Bloody--
[clears throat]

37:44.428 --> 37:46.722
- Sally, I must
do the rounds.

37:48.182 --> 37:49.642
Hello.
- Darling.

37:49.725 --> 37:50.851
- Ha!

37:50.935 --> 37:52.269
- He likes you.

38:08.577 --> 38:11.497
[dark music]

38:11.580 --> 38:18.004
♪ ♪

38:19.130 --> 38:20.464
[door slams]

38:24.218 --> 38:26.804
- Hello.
- Ah. Hello, love.

38:26.887 --> 38:28.222
Sorry, I didn't mean
to startle you.

38:28.306 --> 38:30.474
I, um--I let myself in
to save time.

38:31.600 --> 38:32.977
You must be
the lovely Virginia.

38:33.060 --> 38:34.395
Alfred Pennyworth.

38:35.479 --> 38:39.191
- Hi.
Yes, Virginia Devereaux.

38:39.275 --> 38:41.318
- Nice to meet you.
- Mm.

38:41.402 --> 38:42.611
- Your old man about, is he?

38:42.695 --> 38:44.238
- Uh, yes.

38:44.321 --> 38:47.199
Please, come this way,
Mr. Pennyworth.

38:49.493 --> 38:52.413
Pat, dear, we have a visitor.

38:52.496 --> 38:55.166
- Mr. Pennyworth.
[grunts]

38:56.459 --> 38:59.545
Is Thomas safe?
- Snug as a dormouse,

38:59.628 --> 39:01.839
somewhere over the Atlantic.

39:01.922 --> 39:04.383
- Thank you.
- Let's settle up, shall we?

39:04.467 --> 39:06.302
Do you need an invoice?

39:06.385 --> 39:08.763
- Oh, right.
No.

39:08.846 --> 39:12.058
- £10,000 down,
£990,000 outstanding.

39:12.141 --> 39:14.935
- Are you kidding me?
A million pounds?

39:15.019 --> 39:16.562
- Please, Virginia,
let me handle this.

39:16.645 --> 39:18.481
- You are the dumbest,
softest son of a bitch

39:18.564 --> 39:19.899
I ever saw.

39:19.982 --> 39:22.735
A million to save
that useless trust fund baby?

39:22.818 --> 39:25.946
- It was the right thing to do.
He's weak.

39:26.030 --> 39:27.490
He would have betrayed me,
testified against me.

39:27.573 --> 39:30.493
I couldn't let him do that.
- He was weak?

39:30.576 --> 39:32.453
[chuckles]
- Here, hang on, miss.

39:32.536 --> 39:34.205
Let's get business
out of the way first, shall we?

39:34.288 --> 39:36.665
- Take a hike.
He's not paying you.

39:36.749 --> 39:38.084
- Oh, he'll pay.

39:38.167 --> 39:40.294
Or I'll start talking
about Lullaby.

39:40.377 --> 39:41.796
You wouldn't like that,
would you, Mr. Wayne?

39:41.879 --> 39:43.798
- What? How?
- Don't say a goddamn word.

39:43.881 --> 39:45.299
[door slams]

39:45.382 --> 39:47.176
- Oh, for fuck's sake,
you were supposed to wait.

39:47.259 --> 39:48.469
- Thomas?
- I haven't got

39:48.552 --> 39:49.887
anything out of him yet.
- [grunts]

39:49.970 --> 39:51.514
- Oh.
- You tell me it isn't true.

39:51.597 --> 39:52.973
- It is not that simple, son.
- Tell me you didn't try

39:53.057 --> 39:54.350
to make me kill
my own wife!

39:54.433 --> 39:55.559
- No, no, I didn't!

39:55.643 --> 39:57.186
- You had nothing
to do with it?

39:57.269 --> 39:59.688
- It's complicated.
- My daughter was in the house!

39:59.772 --> 40:00.815
Have you no shame at all?

40:00.898 --> 40:02.233
No morals?
No conscience?

40:02.316 --> 40:04.318
- Wasn't me.
It was her.

40:04.402 --> 40:06.654
- What?
- It was her.

40:06.737 --> 40:08.489
She's CIA.

40:08.572 --> 40:10.491
She's--she's my handler.

40:10.574 --> 40:13.077
She made me do all of this.

40:13.160 --> 40:15.371
- You spineless
son of a bitch.

40:15.454 --> 40:17.123
- Oh, go ahead,
shoot me.

40:17.206 --> 40:19.583
Send me to prison.
I don't care anymore.

40:19.667 --> 40:23.003
I am tired
of this whole goddamn charade.

40:23.087 --> 40:25.339
- You couldn't keep your nerve
for one more day?

40:25.422 --> 40:26.340
- [sighs]

40:26.423 --> 40:28.092
- [scoffs]

40:28.175 --> 40:29.135
[gun cocking]

40:29.218 --> 40:31.220
Sit down.
All of you.

40:32.596 --> 40:34.515
- Well, here's a turnup, eh?

40:39.937 --> 40:42.815
- Why the hell do you have
a CIA handler?

40:42.898 --> 40:45.860
- I made some mistakes.
- Mistakes?

40:45.943 --> 40:47.444
- Errors of judgment.

40:47.528 --> 40:49.029
- Fraud, corruption,

40:49.113 --> 40:51.365
sexual assault.

40:51.448 --> 40:52.825
- It was entrapment.

40:52.908 --> 40:55.119
The CIA wanted our pharma wing.

40:55.202 --> 40:57.204
- And your father
was a weak link.

40:57.288 --> 40:58.539
- Just curious,

40:58.622 --> 41:00.833
why's the CIA messing about
with drugs?

41:00.916 --> 41:02.501
There's easier ways to kill.

41:02.585 --> 41:04.503
- We've barely scratched
the surface

41:04.587 --> 41:06.380
of what we can do
with this drug.

41:06.463 --> 41:10.176
Give it to 5 people,
10 people, 20,

41:10.259 --> 41:12.928
a whole army,
a whole country.

41:13.012 --> 41:15.890
Imagine they all have
the same vision.

41:15.973 --> 41:18.934
A vision controlled by you.

41:19.018 --> 41:21.854
- You sick bitch.
- I'm a patriot and a realist.

41:21.937 --> 41:23.397
And I'm trying to contain
a dangerous

41:23.480 --> 41:25.149
international security
situation.

41:25.232 --> 41:26.233
- Bollocks.

41:26.317 --> 41:28.277
You've cocked up
good and proper.

41:28.360 --> 41:31.071
And now you're trying to save
your ass as best you can.

41:31.155 --> 41:33.574
No shame in that.
But what's the plan here?

41:33.657 --> 41:34.950
Are you gonna shoot us
or something?

41:35.034 --> 41:36.285
'Cause I've got a gun as well

41:36.368 --> 41:38.329
if that's where we're going.
- Try me.

41:39.330 --> 41:41.457
- I'm just saying.
[sniffs]

41:41.540 --> 41:43.042
- We're going home.

41:43.125 --> 41:45.669
You're staying here
for the police to deal with.

41:45.753 --> 41:47.046
- Well, I'll tell them
everything.

41:47.129 --> 41:48.923
- The government
won't want to hear it.

41:49.006 --> 41:51.467
America is an ally.

41:51.550 --> 41:54.386
You guys are
much better culprits.

41:54.470 --> 41:56.680
Patrick, there's
some handcuffs in my purse.

41:59.391 --> 42:02.645
- Dad, whatever it is
you've done wrong,

42:02.728 --> 42:04.396
this isn't the way
to fix things.

42:04.480 --> 42:06.106
- [sighs]
I have no choice.

42:06.190 --> 42:08.442
- Everybody has a choice, Dad.
[door crashes open]

42:08.525 --> 42:10.194
- Police. Hands up.

42:10.277 --> 42:12.029
Drop the gun.

42:12.112 --> 42:14.156
- Drop the gun.

42:14.240 --> 42:17.201
[tense music]

42:17.284 --> 42:19.203
♪ ♪

42:19.286 --> 42:20.579
- What are you doing here?

42:20.663 --> 42:21.956
We didn't call the police.

42:22.039 --> 42:24.667
- No, that was me.

42:24.750 --> 42:27.628
I guess I could have mentioned.

42:27.711 --> 42:29.880
- You're all under arrest.

42:29.964 --> 42:32.716
- See, the plan was to get
Mr. Wayne here to confess,

42:32.800 --> 42:34.885
then find out
where this Lullaby was stashed.

42:34.969 --> 42:37.221
Only Thomas here couldn't wait.

42:38.722 --> 42:40.724
Anyway,
turns out, it was you.

42:40.808 --> 42:42.685
- We have done nothing wrong.

42:42.768 --> 42:44.728
These men are fugitives.

42:44.812 --> 42:45.938
- Just following orders, madam.

42:46.021 --> 42:48.565
- Who's the dumb
motherfucker now?

42:48.649 --> 42:50.276
Scorched Earth, my ass.

42:50.359 --> 42:53.362
- Keep your mouth shut.
We'll be out before breakfast.

42:53.445 --> 42:55.698
- Hey, give us a moment.

42:55.781 --> 42:57.408
What do you mean,
Scorched Earth?

42:57.491 --> 42:58.993
Sounds ominous.

42:59.076 --> 43:00.995
- Tell them, Officer Devereaux,
tell them.

43:01.078 --> 43:02.496
You have diplomatic immunity.

43:02.579 --> 43:04.707
- Shut your goddamn mouth.

43:04.790 --> 43:07.751
It's too late anyway.
I already sent them.

43:07.835 --> 43:09.628
I have no way to call them off.

43:09.712 --> 43:11.380
- What's too late?

43:11.463 --> 43:13.882
- She sent men
to finish Martha.

43:13.966 --> 43:21.056
♪ ♪

43:25.436 --> 43:27.146
[guns cocking]

43:28.355 --> 43:29.857
- Good evening, gentlemen.

43:31.984 --> 43:33.986
- Sorry.

43:34.069 --> 43:35.195
Wrong room.

43:40.326 --> 43:42.077
- That was them.

43:42.161 --> 43:44.955
You should have seen
their faces as they left.

43:45.039 --> 43:46.332
Very droll.

43:46.415 --> 43:49.418
- That was them.
She's safe.

43:49.501 --> 43:50.878
They're gone.

43:50.961 --> 43:53.255
I hope we can see
our way past this, Mr. Aziz.

43:53.339 --> 43:55.758
I am the one
who called you lot.

43:55.841 --> 43:58.719
- Yes, we'll see.
- Glad to hear it.

43:58.802 --> 44:01.513
Thank you, Constable.
We can go now.

44:04.058 --> 44:06.018
Million bloody quid
you cost me.

44:06.101 --> 44:08.228
And are you happy now
now you got the truth?

44:08.312 --> 44:11.231
[bright music]

44:11.315 --> 44:13.567
♪ ♪

44:13.650 --> 44:15.027
We get this sorted,
you gents should come

44:15.110 --> 44:16.904
down to Queen Anne's.

44:16.987 --> 44:19.531
We treat plods like you
just the same as anyone else.

44:19.615 --> 44:21.367
Point of pride.

44:21.450 --> 44:24.370
[siren wailing]

44:24.453 --> 44:31.543
♪ ♪

44:37.841 --> 44:40.386
- [moans]
Oh, yeah.

44:40.469 --> 44:41.595
Say it again.

44:41.678 --> 44:44.264
- Oh, you're
a dirty wee gadget,

44:44.348 --> 44:45.432
and you know you are.

44:45.516 --> 44:46.517
Oh, Jesus Christ.

44:46.600 --> 44:48.477
[door slams]
- [chuckles]

44:48.560 --> 44:49.770
- Who the fuck's here?

44:49.853 --> 44:52.272
- Only me.
Didn't mean to disturb.

44:52.356 --> 44:54.358
- Alfie.
- Who is it?

44:56.360 --> 44:58.612
- Alfie, Sally.

44:58.695 --> 45:01.031
Sally, Alfie.

45:01.115 --> 45:03.951
- Nice to meet you.
- Likewise.

45:07.413 --> 45:08.539
- Well, I was just
up to the office,

45:08.622 --> 45:10.457
so don't let me interrupt.

45:10.541 --> 45:12.334
- Nice to meet you, Alfie.

45:12.418 --> 45:14.628
[chuckles]

45:14.711 --> 45:17.881
[laughter]
Here we go.

45:17.965 --> 45:20.884
[dramatic music]

45:20.968 --> 45:28.058
♪ ♪

45:29.393 --> 45:33.147
- [sighs]
Now I'm stuck.

45:33.230 --> 45:35.190
[sniffs]

45:35.274 --> 45:36.775
- Makes two of us.

45:38.485 --> 45:41.238
- Sandra?
How'd you get in here?

45:41.321 --> 45:43.449
- Chadley let me in
to wait for you.

45:45.200 --> 45:47.161
- Huh.
- I went to leave,

45:47.244 --> 45:50.205
but then Daveboy and that girl
were downstairs.

45:50.289 --> 45:51.582
Didn't want to interrupt.

45:51.665 --> 45:53.750
- Right.

45:53.834 --> 45:55.043
Sorry.

45:55.127 --> 45:56.587
- It's all right.

45:56.670 --> 45:57.838
This is nice.

46:01.216 --> 46:02.259
- Hmm.

46:20.277 --> 46:21.862
- You look tired.

46:21.945 --> 46:23.280
- Long day.

46:23.363 --> 46:26.909
Had a bit of a misunderstanding
with the police.

46:26.992 --> 46:28.577
It's all sorted now.

46:30.329 --> 46:32.080
- What?
Were you arrested?

46:32.164 --> 46:33.916
- Detained.

46:35.626 --> 46:38.128
- What did they detain you for?

46:38.212 --> 46:39.880
- For allegedly breaking
Thomas Wayne

46:39.963 --> 46:41.548
out of the Tower of London.

46:41.632 --> 46:44.593
- Uh, did you
break Thomas Wayne

46:44.676 --> 46:46.720
out of the Tower of London?

46:46.803 --> 46:48.222
- Yeah, we did.

46:50.974 --> 46:53.769
- What was
the misunderstanding, then?

46:53.852 --> 46:55.062
- Well, when you put it
like that,

46:55.145 --> 46:56.855
I'm not sure there was one.

46:56.939 --> 46:58.398
- [chuckles]

46:58.482 --> 47:01.068
- Everyone just sort of decided

47:01.151 --> 47:03.904
I'd done the right thing
in the end.

47:03.987 --> 47:06.907
[poignant music]

47:06.990 --> 47:08.242
♪ ♪

47:08.325 --> 47:10.744
- How do you do it, Alfie?

47:10.827 --> 47:12.371
- Do what?

47:15.541 --> 47:17.709
- Get away with things.

47:19.211 --> 47:22.464
It's been years...

47:22.548 --> 47:24.383
and you haven't changed a bit.

47:27.344 --> 47:29.805
- Well...

47:29.888 --> 47:31.390
not like you have.

47:33.642 --> 47:35.852
- No.

47:35.936 --> 47:42.776
♪ ♪

47:43.652 --> 47:47.030
Being round you again,

47:47.114 --> 47:48.240
I feel the same.

47:53.870 --> 47:54.830
- Sandra, I can't--

47:54.913 --> 47:56.331
- I'm not--

48:01.837 --> 48:03.463
I'm not asking for anything.

48:03.547 --> 48:10.637
♪ ♪

48:38.040 --> 48:40.334
- [snoring]

48:44.713 --> 48:46.048
Hello?

48:49.176 --> 48:50.469
Hello?

48:53.430 --> 48:54.806
Is anyone there?

48:57.267 --> 49:00.687
[tense music]

49:00.771 --> 49:04.274
This is not what we agreed!

49:04.358 --> 49:09.613
♪ ♪

49:09.696 --> 49:12.366
- Dr. Glubb, it's so nice
to finally meet you.

49:17.287 --> 49:19.289
I'm a huge admirer
of your work.

49:19.373 --> 49:26.463
♪ ♪

49:33.136 --> 49:35.389
We're going to do
great things together.

49:35.472 --> 49:38.266
♪ ♪
